ENTRY            A0605   20260204   20260401   20260401       A131
SUBENT        A0605001   20260204   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                 14         45
TITLE      Study of excitation functions in Rh(alpha,xn)Ag
           reactions
AUTHOR     (M.Afzal Ansari,N.P.M.Sathik,B.P.Singh,
           M.G.V.Sankaracharyulu,R.Prasad)
INSTITUTE  (3ZZZTPT,3INDMUA)
REFERENCE  (J,IMP/E,5,345,1996)
           (C,92BOMBAY,,224,1992)
REL-REF    (R,,L.C.Northcliffe+,J,ND/A,7,233,1970) Stopping power
           data.
           (R,,C.M.Lederer+,B,LEDERER-7,,,1970)
FACILITY   (ISOCY,3INDVEC) Variable Energy Cyclotron at VECC,
           Calcutta, India.
SAMPLE     Rhodium foils of thickness 1.24 mg/cm2 each. The purity
           of the material was better than 99.9%.
           Aluminium degraders of thickness 6.25 mg/cm2 were
           used for degrading the alpha-particle beam incident
           on individual foils.
DETECTOR   (GELI) A high resolution (FWHM 2 keV at 1.33 MeV)
           100 cm3 ORTEC Ge(Li) detector, coupled with a
           precalibrated 4096 channel CARBERRA-88 analyzer and
           associated electronics. 152Eu standard gamma source of
           known strength was used for energy and efficiency
           calibration, by keeping it at target position.
METHOD     (BCINT,STTA) Six rhodium foils were used.
           (ACTIV) Irradiation and cooling times are unknown
           (GSPEC) Number of measurements and its duration are
           unknown.
COMMENT    The measured excitation functions for the reactions
           are the weighted average of the cross sections values
           corresponding to various identified gamma-rays, weak
           gamma-rays, as well as gamma-rays having energies
           higher than 1.5 MeV, are not taken into consideration
           because of their low detection efficiencies.
ADD-RES    (COMP) Pre-Equilibrium Model, Geometry Dependent
           Hibrid Model.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
STATUS     (TABLE,,M.Afzal Ansari+,J,IMP/E,5,345,1996) Tbl.1
HISTORY    (19980706C) By F.C.
           (19980707U) Last checking has been done.
           (19990318A)DATE is corrected
           (20170206U) SD: Institute corrected. Ref. 92BOMBAY was
           added. Small corrections in all Subents. Ref. in
           REL-REF was corrected: R.C.Northcliffe+,J,ND/A,7,256 ->
           L.C.Northcliffe+,J,ND/A,7,233. ERR-T -> DATA-ERR.
           (20260204U) SD: Small corrections in Subent 001.
ENDBIB              45
